    "Where Hyperbolic ProtoNets are effective in few-shot settings, a number of works have also investigated prototype-based solutions for the general classification.",
    "As starting point, these works commonly assume that the classes in a dataset are organized in a hierarchy, see Fig. 5.",
    "Long et al. (2020) embed action class hierarchy H in hyperbolic space using hyperbolic entailment cones (Ganea et al., 2018a), with an additional loss to increase the angular separation between leaf nodes to avoid interlabel confusion amongst class labels Y.",
